content:
The chunk demonstrates how to create an independent scene graph in C++ by reparenting a camera node path to a new NodePath named "render2" and loading a model into this custom scene, enabling the rendering of a separate 3D environment distinct from the default render scene.

cpp

// View some other scene, unrelated to render
NodePath render2("render2");  // the string parameter is important
camNP.reparent_to(render2);
NodePath env = windowFramework->load_model(render2, "environment.egg");
